==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foxglove
<hw>Fox"glove`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>foxes-gl⟦omac⟧fa</ets>,
<ets>foxes-cl⟦omac⟧fa</ets>,<ets>foxes-clife</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any plant of the genus <gen>Digitalis</gen>. The
common English foxglove (<spn>Digitalis purpurea</spn>) is a handsome
perennial or biennial plant, whose leaves are used as a powerful
medicine, both as a sedative and diuretic. See
<er>Digitalis</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pan through the pastures oftentimes hath run⟦br⟧
To pluck the speckled <qex>foxgloves</qex> from their stem.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>foxhole</ent>⟦br⟧
